2. General Rules for Subnet CIDR
‚úî Public = usually /24
‚úî Private = usually /24
‚úî DB = /24
‚úî NAT / LB = /28
‚úî ALWAYS different availability zones me

Requirement	Allowed?	Notes
Public + Private in same AZ	‚úÖ Yes	Perfect design
Use same CIDR  for multiple public subnets	‚ùå No	Each subnet must have unique CIDR
Use same CIDR  for multiple private subnets	‚ùå No	Each subnet must have unique CIDR
Use same CIDR  for multiple public and private subnets	‚ùå No	Each subnet must have unique CIDR



3. Final Summary (Absolutely Correct)
‚≠ê If VPC = 10.0.0.0/16

‚û° Subnets 10.0.0.0/24, 10.0.1.0/24, 10.0.2.0/24 ‚Ä¶

‚≠ê If VPC = 10.1.0.0/16

‚û° Subnets 10.1.0.0/24, 10.1.1.0/24, 10.1.2.0/24 ‚Ä¶

‚≠ê If VPC = 10.5.0.0/16

‚û° Subnets 10.5.0.0/24, 10.5.1.0/24, 10.5.2.0/24 ‚Ä¶


‚≠ê If VPC = 10.0.0.0/16

‚û° Valid subnets:
10.0.0.0/24 ‚Üí 10.0.255.0/24
(Yani 10.0.X.0/24 where X = 0 to 255)

‚≠ê If VPC = 10.1.0.0/16

‚û° Valid subnets:
10.1.0.0/24 ‚Üí 10.1.255.0/24
(Yani 10.1.X.0/24 where X = 0 to 255)

‚≠ê If VPC = 10.5.0.0/16

‚û° Valid subnets:
10.5.0.0/24 ‚Üí 10.5.255.0/24
(Yani 10.5.X.0/24 where X = 0 to 255)


üß† Final Master Rule
‚úî Valid VPC CIDR = 10.X.0.0 /16 ‚Üí /28

Where:

X = 0 to 255

Last 2 octets = 0.0
